<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1866,2035]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1938,1963]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[496,640,1939,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorea">
<emphasis box="[496,640,1939,1963]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. marmorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The combination of three golden shiny fasciae on the forewing, short lobes of vinculum, bilobed uncus with each lobe bearing two-three papillae, and numerous large cornuti on the vesica distinguishes 
<taxonomicName box="[422,564,2011,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruanica">
<emphasis box="[422,564,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. peruanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[732,837,2010,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,837,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,367,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,207,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 33. Adults of the central Andean Nepticulidae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/557163/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Puplesis" box="[549,866,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Puplesis, R. &amp; Robinson, G. S. (2000) A review of the Central and South American Nepticulidae (Lepidoptera) with special reference to Belize. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, London (Entomology), 69 (1), 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="2000">Puplesis &amp; Robinson 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 27–28, fig. 19. Forewing length about 
<quantity box="[1339,1432,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
; wingspan about 
<quantity box="[335,423,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
